---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { getAsset } from '~/utils/permalinks';

const metadata = {
  title: 'RSS Feeds - Subscribe to Updates',
  description: 'Learn how to subscribe to our blog posts and newsletters via RSS',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 mx-auto lg:px-8 lg:py-20 max-w-4xl">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1
        class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-tighter tracking-tighter mb-4 font-heading text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100"
      >
        Subscribe via RSS
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-muted dark:text-slate-300">
        Stay up to date with our latest blog posts and newsletters using RSS feeds.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>What is RSS?</h2>
      <p>
        RSS (Really Simple Syndication) is a way to stay updated with your favorite websites without having to visit
        them individually. Instead of checking our site for new content, you can use an RSS reader to get notifications
        when we publish new posts.
      </p>

      <h2>Our RSS Feeds</h2>
      <p>We offer three separate RSS feeds so you can subscribe to exactly what interests you:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 space-y-4">
        <div class="border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">Blog Posts Feed</h3>
          <p class="text-muted dark:text-slate-300 mb-3">
            Get updates on all our latest blog articles, tutorials, and insights.
          </p>
          <a href={getAsset('/rss.xml')} class="inline-flex items-center text-primary hover:underline font-medium">
            {getAsset('/rss.xml')}
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">Newsletter Feed</h3>
          <p class="text-muted dark:text-slate-300 mb-3">
            Subscribe to our newsletter issues for curated content and updates.
          </p>
          <a
            href={getAsset('/newsletter-rss.xml')}
            class="inline-flex items-center text-primary hover:underline font-medium"
          >
            {getAsset('/newsletter-rss.xml')}
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">Events Feed</h3>
          <p class="text-muted dark:text-slate-300 mb-3">
            Never miss an upcoming event! Get notified about our meetups and community gatherings.
          </p>
          <a
            href={getAsset('/events-rss.xml')}
            class="inline-flex items-center text-primary hover:underline font-medium"
          >
            {getAsset('/events-rss.xml')}
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>How to Subscribe</h2>

      <h3>Step 1: Choose an RSS Reader</h3>
      <p>First, you'll need an RSS reader application. Here are some popular options:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Feedly</strong> - Web-based, great for beginners (<a
            href="https://feedly.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">feedly.com</a
          >)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>NewsBlur</strong> - Web and mobile apps (<a
            href="https://newsblur.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">newsblur.com</a
          >)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Inoreader</strong> - Powerful features, web and mobile (<a
            href="https://www.inoreader.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">inoreader.com</a
          >)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>NetNewsWire</strong> - Free, open-source (Mac/iOS) (<a
            href="https://netnewswire.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">netnewswire.com</a
          >)
        </li>
        <li><strong>Thunderbird</strong> - Email client with built-in RSS reader</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Step 2: Add Our Feed</h3>
      <p>Once you have an RSS reader:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Copy the feed URL you want to subscribe to (see links above)</li>
        <li>Open your RSS reader</li>
        <li>Look for an "Add Feed" or "Subscribe" button (usually a + icon)</li>
        <li>Paste the feed URL</li>
        <ol>
          <li>Blogs: <a href="https://boston-wib.org/rss.xml">https://boston-wib.org/rss.xml</a></li>
          <li>
            Newsletters: <a href="https://boston-wib.org/newsletter-rss.xml"
              >https://boston-wib.org/newsletter-rss.xml</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>Events: <a href="https://boston-wib.org/events-rss.xml">https://boston-wib.org/events-rss.xml</a></li>
        </ol>
        <li>Click "Subscribe" or "Add"</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Step 3: Enjoy!</h3>
      <p>
        That's it! You'll now receive updates whenever we publish new content. You can subscribe to one or both feeds
        depending on your interests.
      </p>

      <h2>Need Help?</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about RSS or need help subscribing, feel free to reach out to us. We're happy to help you
        stay connected!
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
